                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14466049" author="shemnon" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2008 08:44:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix for 1.6.1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466215" author="aalmiray" created="Wed, 7 Jan 2009 22:33:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While an attributeDelegate could solve many cases there are other two scenarios that have to be taken into consideration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;factories expecting a String while calling newInstance()&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;value could be a GString&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;#1 is easily fixed with a preInstantiateDelegate instead of an attributeDelegate&lt;br/&gt;
#2 could be solved also with a preInstantiateDelegate but only if we change the contract of the delegates, as the value is actually immutable right now, FBS.preInstantiate() must now return a value.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466301" author="shemnon" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2009 09:49:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed it in the factories.  A global fix may not be desired in all cases (GSQL for instance want to know GStrings from Strings).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Action widgets, text widgets, look and feel, and arbitrary strings to text attributes also fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
